<subSubSection id="C337088DF768B129B182FAC4363F446B" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F768B129B182FAC4311A4447" blockId="29.[151,1437,1195,1869]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F768B129B182FAC432C24610" box="[199,251,1339,1365]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F768B129B039FAC430B04617" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[380,649,1338,1365]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 102)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned both male and female in his type description. His acquisition catalogue lists 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF768B129B0FCFAA03051463B" box="[441,616,1375,1401]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
received from Wahlberg. Possible 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F768B129B54EFAA0364B463B" box="[1035,1138,1375,1401]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">syntypes</typeStatus>
are two older specimens received in 1837 from Jacob Letterstedt (1796–1862), the Swedish-Norwegian Consul in 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F768B129B585FA7C36C546DF" box="[1216,1276,1411,1437]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Cape</collectingRegion>
Town. These were identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F768B129B031FA5830714683" box="[372,584,1447,1473]" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palpebrosa">
<emphasis id="B9598714F768B129B031FA5830714683" box="[372,584,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Sylvia palpebrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but later corrected by Sundevall to 
<emphasis id="B9598714F768B129B2BCFA5836DB4682" box="[1017,1250,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F768B129B2BCFA5836E74682" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[1017,1246,1447,1472]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="capensis">Zosterops capensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF768B129B464FA5832EC46A7" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
figured by Levaillant (1802, plate 132) should also be part of the original type series. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F768B129B5BAFA34332A454B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="29" pageNumber="550" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 35)</bibRefCitation>
refers to NRM 568711 [4578] as a “type”; we treat this as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F768B129B28AFA103602454B" box="[975,1083,1519,1545]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this study skin of an adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F768B129B095F9EC30BC456F" box="[464,645,1555,1581]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" value="1839-03-13">
13 March 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F768B129B30FF9EC30BC456F" box="[586,645,1555,1581]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67106" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" unit="in" value="1839.0">1839</quantity>
</date>
in Rondebosch. The 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF768B129B2C4F9EC3659456F" box="[897,1120,1555,1581]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">five paralectotypes</specimenCount>
are: NRM 568712 [4579], a study skin of an adult female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F768B129B33FF9C831174513" box="[634,814,1591,1617]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" value="1839-03-21">
21 March 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F768B129B3B6F9C831174513" box="[755,814,1591,1617]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67106" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" unit="in" value="1839.0">1839</quantity>
</date>
in Rondebosch; NRM 90140118 [4210], a male collected before 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F768B129B07EF9A433AE4537" box="[315,407,1627,1653]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66598" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" unit="in" value="1837.0">1837 in</quantity>
the 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F768B129B088F9A430304537" box="[461,521,1627,1653]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Cape</collectingRegion>
area (only “Cap” given) by J. Letterstedt; an unsexed specimen [4209] also collected before 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F768B129B01BF980338145DB" box="[350,440,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66598" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" unit="in" value="1837.0">1837 in</quantity>
the 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F768B129B0A8F980301045DB" box="[493,553,1663,1689]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Cape</collectingRegion>
area by Letterstedt and sent on exchange to Berlin in 1853 (but not found in the ZMB database); and finally the 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF768B129B31CF95C313F45FF" box="[601,774,1699,1725]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
figured by Levaillant (1802, plate 132). Specimens collected by Levaillant in 
<collectingCountry id="F33A1B96F768B129B0E9F938307B45A3" box="[428,578,1735,1761]" name="South Africa" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">South Africa</collectingCountry>
are scattered in several museum collections (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F768B129B509F938371145A3" author="Rookmaaker, L. C." box="[1100,1320,1735,1761]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" refId="ref29509" refString="Rookmaaker, L. C. (1989) The Zoological Exploration of Southern Africa, 1650 - 1790. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, 368 pp." type="book" year="1989">Rookmaaker 1989</bibRefCitation>
). We have not attempted to trace Levaillant’s 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F768B129B36DF91430A24446" box="[552,667,1771,1796]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9598714F768B129B36DF91430A24446" box="[552,667,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Zosterops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F768B129B182F8F0363F446B" blockId="29.[151,1437,1195,1869]" box="[199,1030,1807,1833]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">
